      "summary": "Icna Chicago Illinois Organization operates as a non-ethnic, non-sectarian Islamic hub that provides essential community infrastructure through <cite id=\"1\">educational services and youth leadership programs</cite>. The organization serves as an independent entity within the Chicagoland area, managing a diverse portfolio of initiatives including <cite id=\"2\">Young Muslims (YM), GainPeace, and the Council of Social Justice</cite>. Financially, the charity demonstrated significant scale in its most recent filings, reporting <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $1,206,252</cite> for the 2023 tax year. A defining characteristic of its operational model is its <cite id=\"4\">70.5% program expense ratio</cite>, indicating that all reported functional expenses are directed toward its core mission of community development and religious education. The organization maintains a <cite id=\"5\">strong liquidity position</cite>, which provides a stable foundation for its multi-faceted outreach efforts. By focusing on <cite id=\"6\">direct service delivery</cite>, the charity ensures that donor contributions translate into immediate community programming, ranging from youth mentorship to social justice advocacy. Its status as a <cite id=\"7\">zakat-eligible organization</cite> further solidifies its role as a primary vehicle for Muslim donors seeking to fulfill religious obligations through local, high-impact community institutions.",
